<br>
Seriously, you'll need to stay in his face for most of the battle. If you let him back off and heal/root/stun, you're letting him maximize his abilities. He'll probably channel through some of your attacks, but if you stick in his face and keep pounding away, you'll have a better chance of interrupting his casting. If your bash is fairly high and you're comfortable with switching in a shield for a moment, you're in even better shape.<br>
<br>
110 MR is respectable, but you might want to get a bit more in there without sacrificing too much HP/AC. Stuns and blinds are not fun - not fun for you, anyway. =) Also, nightmare hide (drops in PoF, I think?) has 5 charges of a cure blind spell. Very nice.<br>
<br>
He's going to LoH himself. Just resolve yourself to that, and try not to get too discouraged when he does so.<br>
<br>
If you can borrow/have access to a regen item - an Iksar CP, a Fungi Tunic, etc. - or any weapons with lifetaps/dots - a Bloodpoint, a Bloodfire, etc. - use and abuse them. They're quite nice in duels.<br>
<br>
Also, shaman alchemy potions may give you the necessary edge. Damage shield, chloro, and stamina potions, albeit somewhat expensive, wouldn't hurt. Just watch out for dispells.<br>
<br>
I'm sure someone else will be able to offer more advice. Good luck! <p><html><body>
