Some of this is a bit cheezy, but...<br>
<br>
1). Use the water.  If you are in the water and he isn't, he can't cast on you, and verse visa.  Yah, it's kinda cheezy, but you can jump off the dock when you see him starting to cast nastyness on you.<br>
<br>
2). Kill holgresh in WL and load up on mojo sticks, especially the frost strike ones.  They have 5 charges, 2 second cast from inventory, good damage, I think it has a stun component, and the pally probably won't have much/any cold resist gear on.<br>
<br>
3). Get a couple totems of ralfon zek from stonebrunt; they have a right click stun with a fairly short cast time.<br>
<br>
4). If possible, land a tash on him with a journeyman's walking stick, then use the webs from perma or crystal caverns to get him snared.  Do this BEFORE you debuff him, so the snare is at the end of his buff list. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5). This one is super fun; ask him to group with you before the fight, so you can talk w/o using tells or say.  Some people still fall for this, lets you use /follow so they can't bugger off and hide to med/regen. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If he won't, use invis potions if you need a short break from the fight (unless he has see invis item).<br>
<br>
6). Shammy potions RULE; the DS is a given, but the other good one you can get is the ice giant toe one.   It does a 300pt heal each use, and is instant cast.  With a few 10 charge ones that's an extra 3000 hp x number of potions... not as good as the old soulfires, but still pretty respectable.<br>
<br>
7). Speaking of soulfires, verify he won't be using one before the fight; there's no way you can beat a pally that can instant CH 5 times during the fight... just like there wasnt' any way one could beat ME when warriors could use em.  /rude verant for nerfing em, bastards.  There's also a CH potion from paw, hard to get tho.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Might want to pick up a deathbeetle gland from sol b; if it sticks, it'll mess him up fairly well.<br>
<br>
9). Do the gnollslayer quest and get the sword; it has 2 charges of the level 34 shaman pet.  Won't do all that much damage, BUT it will bird dog him so he can't hide as easily, and it will help interrupt his casting. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
10). Spend a few hours in the arena or dueling and practice jousting with a friend.  There's lots of timing involved, and a few tricks.  Get the feel for it.<br>
<br>
